;A TRIS SOLVENT MOLECULE (RESIDUE 309) IS BOUND IN THE
ACTIVE SITE TO THE HG CATION AT 40% OCCUPANCY, AND A WATER
MOLECULE IS ALSO BOUND TO THE HG CATION AT 60% OCCUPANCY.

THERE ARE THREE OTHER BINDING SITES FOR MERCURY CATIONS
ON CPA (RESIDUES 316 - 318).

AN ADDITIONAL CATION IS BOUND TO GLU 270, AND IS
ARBITRARILY LABELLED A COPPER CATION.
